50
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:01,581
The key is to think of all light

51
00:02:01,581 --> 00:02:03,371
as a mixture of colors.

52
00:02:03,371 --> 00:02:05,858
Sir Isaac Newton famously
demonstrated this

53
00:02:05,858 --> 00:02:08,932
when he used a glass prism
to break up sunlight.

54
00:02:08,932 --> 00:02:11,637
When sunlight passes in
and out of the prism,

55
00:02:11,637 --> 00:02:13,310
it bends, or refracts,

56
00:02:13,310 --> 00:02:16,263
and splits up into a spectrum of colors.

57
00:02:16,263 --> 00:02:19,151
After Newton, other scientists discovered

58
00:02:19,151 --> 00:02:22,002
that the light's wavelength
is what determines

59
00:02:22,002 --> 00:02:25,130
how much it will refract,
and what color it will be.

60
00:02:25,130 --> 00:02:28,996
Bluer light has a shorter
wavelength and bends more.

61
00:02:28,996 --> 00:02:33,032
Redder light, with longer
wavelengths, bends less.

62
00:02:33,032 --> 00:02:34,462
And this is the key point.

63
00:02:34,462 --> 00:02:35,889
Sunlight looks white

64
00:02:35,889 --> 00:02:38,889
because it contains all visible colors.

65
00:02:38,889 --> 00:02:41,568
