66
00:02:41,568 --> 00:02:44,098
to easily visualize the colors contained

67
00:02:44,098 --> 00:02:46,995
in any given light source.

68
00:02:46,995 --> 00:02:50,241
In this graph, along the
X-axis, is the wavelength,

69
00:02:50,241 --> 00:02:54,705
and along the Y-axis is the
intensity of that wavelength.

70
00:02:54,705 --> 00:02:59,412
For example, here's the graph
of what daylight looks like.

71
00:02:59,412 --> 00:03:03,288
This is known as the spectrum of daylight.

72
00:03:03,288 --> 00:03:05,184
And a graph like this is called

73
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:08,425
a spectral power distribution.

74
